columns.name: LICENSE_NBR
columns.description:
An identification number issued to businesses/individuals to operate legally for the duration of
their license term.

columns.name: LIC_STATUS
columns.description: This indicates whether a sidewalk café license is active or inactive.

columns.name: BUSINESS_NAME
columns.description: The legal business name as filed with the New York State Secretary of State or County Clerk

columns.name: BUSINESS_NAME2
columns.description: If applicable, the Doing-Business-As (DBA)/trade name.

columns.name: BUILDING
columns.description: The building number of the business’s address.

columns.name: STREET
columns.description: The street name of the business’s address.

columns.name: CITY
columns.description: The city where the business is located.

columns.name: STATE
columns.description: The state where the business is located.

columns.name: ZIP
columns.description: The zip code where the business is located.

columns.name: SWC_TYPE
columns.description:
A sidewalk café is a portion of a legal restaurant that operates on the public sidewalk. There are
three types: Enclosed, Unenclosed, and Small Unenclosed.

columns.name: SWC_SQ_FT
columns.description:
This indicates the size of the sidewalk café space by square footage as permitted by the business’s
DCA license.

columns.name: SWC_TABLES
columns.description:
This indicates the maximum number of tables for the sidewalk café space as permitted by the
business’s DCA license.

columns.name: SWC_CHAIRS
columns.description:
This indicates the maximum number of chairs for the sidewalk café space as permitted by the
business’s DCA license.

columns.name: DOHMH
columns.description:
An identification number used by the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene (DOHMH) to
permit a food service establishment to operate its business.

columns.name: FINAL_X
columns.description: X coordinate of business’s address using New York Long Island State Plane.

columns.name: FINAL_Y
columns.description: Y coordinate of business’s address using New York Long Island State Plane.

columns.name: COMMUNITY_DISTRICT
columns.description: The New York City Community District where a business is located.

columns.name: CITY_COUNCIL_DISTRICT
columns.description: The New York City Council District where a business is located.

columns.name: CD_URL
columns.description: The URL for the website of the NYC Community District where a business is located.

columns.name: APP_ID
columns.description: An identification number assigned by DCA to record each application received.

columns.name: APP_SWC_TYPE
columns.description:
A sidewalk café is a portion of a legal restaurant that operates on the public sidewalk. There are
three types: Enclosed, Unenclosed, and Small Unenclosed.

columns.name: APP_SQ_FT
columns.description: The business applied for this amount of square footage space for its sidewalk café.

columns.name: APP_TABLES
columns.description: The business applied for this number of tables for its sidewalk café space.

columns.name: APP_CHAIRS
columns.description: The business applied for this number of chairs for its sidewalk café space.

columns.name: APP_STATUS
columns.description: This indicates the status of a business’s DCA sidewalk café application.

columns.name: APP_STATUS_DATE
columns.description: The date when a business’s DCA sidewalk café application reached its APP_STATUS.

columns.name: EXPIRATION_DATE
columns.description: Expiration date of Temporary Operating Letter or DCA License.

columns.name: APP_TOO_DATE
columns.description:
Expiration date of Temporary Operating Letter. DCA may issue a Temporary Operating Letter to
certain applicants while their license application is being reviewed. This allows the business to
legally operate for a specific time period.

columns.name: SUBMIT_DATE
columns.description:
Latest date when a business pays (a portion of) its submission fee for a DCA sidewalk café license
application.

columns.name: INTAKE
columns.description: Status of DCA receipt of a sidewalk café license application.

columns.name: INTAKE_DD
columns.description: The date when an application’s intake reached its current status.

columns.name: DPQA
columns.description: Status of DCA review of a sidewalk café license application.

columns.name: SEND_PACKAGE_DD
columns.description:
Date when the sidewalk café license application was sent to the relevant Borough President,
Community Board, City Council Member, and Speaker of the Council.

columns.name: CP
columns.description: Status of the NYC Department of City Planning’s review of enclosed sidewalk café applications.

columns.name: CP_DD
columns.description: Date when the application’s Department of City Planning review reached its current status.

columns.name: CB
columns.description: Status of the relevant Community Board’s review of a sidewalk café license application.

columns.name: CB_DD
columns.description: Date when the application’s Community Board review reached its current status.

columns.name: HEARING
columns.description: Status of the public hearing for reviewing sidewalk café license applications.

columns.name: HEARING_DD
columns.description: Date when the application’s public hearing reached its current status.

columns.name: HEARING_PUBLIC
columns.description: If a public hearing is scheduled, value will be “SWC Public Hearing”.

columns.name: HEARING_PUBLIC_DD
columns.description: If applicable, the date when a public hearing is scheduled.

columns.name: CC
columns.description: Status of City Council review of a business’s sidewalk café license application.

columns.name: CC_DD
columns.description: Date when the application’s City Council review reached its current status.

columns.name: MOO
columns.description:
Status of Mayor’s Office of Contract Services (MOCS) review of a business’s sidewalk café
license application.

columns.name: MOO_DD
columns.description: Date when the application’s MOCS review reached its current status.

columns.name: ISSUANCE
columns.description: Status of DCA sidewalk café license issuance.

columns.name: ISSUANCE_DD
columns.description: Date when the application’s issuance reached its current status.

view.description:
NOTE: This dataset reflects a historical program that is no longer active. The NYC Department of Transportation will be responsible for regulating outdoor dining under the new Dining Out program, and will be publishing program data once its available. In the interim, please consult the Open Restaurants dataset.

This dataset features detailed information about sidewalk café license applications and, if applicable, issued licenses.
